{
  "stem": "18626.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 346.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because we had a feeling that he had-- he was like an organizer.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A lot of Lithuanian gentile people used to come to his home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the fact is, anytime you know, the telephone was ringing in our house, customers, because we had a telephone, and he didn't have a telephone.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So when people used to call for him, I used to come into his house and said, Mr.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Mazuras, you are called to the telephone.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were nice to him all these years.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But not after the-- the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "After the war broke out, that same man, Mazuras, gave out all [INAUDIBLE] gentile Lithuanians the weapons.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they got their first ones after six days, when the Germans marched in into Lithuania, did a pogrom in Slabodka.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He didn't kill my mother or our children, but he came to kill my father.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my father was already killed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because he was in the first day, he was going to see if the train is going, and the Lithuanians, already partisans they called themselves, grabbed him right by the train, and they took him away to the Ninth Fort with a lot of other Jewish men, and they killed him later.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "May, they marched in May.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a big change, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's-- for the rich people who had the textile factories and all the big enterprises, it was not too happy, because it was right away taken away by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was made, you know, cooperative factories.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But for the poor people who didn't have anything to lose, the Russians-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they were against religion, of course.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the religious schools were already starting to change.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
